HEADWORD: Dad
<hw>Dad</hw> <pr>(d⟦acr⟧d)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Prob. of Celtic
origin; cf. Ir. <ets>daid</ets>, Gael. <ets>daidein</ets>, W.
<ets>tad</ets>, OL. <ets>tata</ets>, Gr. <grk>ta`ta</grk>,
<grk>te`tta</grk>, Skr. <ets>t⟦amac⟧ta</ets>.]</ety> <def>Father; -- a
word sometimes used by children.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I was never so bethumped with words,⟦br⟧
Since I first called my brother's father <qex>dad</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Daddle</ent>⟦br⟧
